data.content:
noun
plural -ups
[count] :the process of cleaning something
The children helped with the cleanup [=helped to clean up] after the meal. - often used before another noun
The cleanup costs of the oil spill will be in the millions of dollars.
The company's cleanup efforts have been applauded by the town.
adjective
always used before a noun
fourth in the batting order of a baseball team
a cleanup hitter
